E) COVID-19: CARRIERS/CREWS/PASSENGER RESTRICTIONS AND REQUIREMENTS
1. RESTRICTIONS AND REQUIREMENTS
NOTE 1:
CARRIERS MUST PROVIDE INFORMATION REGARDING PASSENGER RESTRICTIONS
AND REQUIREMENTS PUBLISHED BY THE GERMAN FEDERAL MINISTRY
OF HEALTH TO ALL PAX.
NOTE 2:
PLEASE ADVISE PAX TO CHECK TRAVEL RESTRICTIONS, TESTING AND
QUARANTINE OBLIGATIONS PRIOR TO DEPARTURE.
NOTE 3:
DUE TO RECIPROCITY RESERVATIONS ENTRY INTO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC
OF GERMANY IS PROHIBITED TO PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED
IN THE FOLLOWING STATES: CHINA.
THIS DOES NOT APPLY TO:
1. GERMAN CITIZENS,
2. EU CITIZENS,
3. CITIZENS OF LIECHTENSTEIN, SWITZERLAND, NORWAY OR ICELAND,
4.THIRD-COUNTRY NATIONALS WITH CURRENT RIGHT OF RESIDENCE IN

ICELAND,

ABOVE, 
6. PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED IN HONG KONG, MACAO
AND TAIWAN.
PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED IN CHINA ARE PERMITTED TO ENTER
THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY PROVIDED THEY HAVE AN IMPERATIVE 
NEED FOR TRAVEL:
1. HEALTHCARE WORKERS, HEALTH RESEARCHERS AND GERIATRIC CARE
WORKERS,
2. SKILLED AND HIGHLY QUALIFIED FOREIGN WORKERS IF THEIR
EMPLOYMENT AN ECONOMIC PERSPECTIVE AND THE WORK CANNOT BE POSTPONED 
OR PERFORMEDABROAD, 
3. FREIGHT TRANSPORT AND OTHER TRANSPORT PERSONNEL,
4. SEASONAL WORKERS IN AGRICULTURE, 
5. SEAFARERS, 
6. FOREIGN STUDENTS, TRAINEES, VOLUNTEERS,
7. PERSONS IMMIGRATING INTO GERMANY
FOR THE PURPOSE OF JOINING THEIR FAMILIES AND VISITS FOR
URGENT FAMILY REASONS OR SHORT TERM VISITS OF CORE FAMILY MEMBERS
(HUSBAND/WIFE, MINOR CHILDREN, PARENTS OF MINOR CHILDREN) OR
UNMARRIED PARTNERS IN A RELATIONSHIP WITH GERMAN NATIONALS,
PART 2 OF 9
B0085/23 NOTAMN

COUNTRY NATIONAL AND GERMAN NATIONAL/EU CITIZEN) RESIDING TOGETHER
INA THIRD COUNTRY FOR IMPORTANT REASONS, 
8. PERSONS IN NEED OF INTERNATIONAL PROTECTION OR FOR OTHER 
HUMANITARIAN REASONS,
9. DIPLOMATS, STAFF OF INTERNATIONAL ORGANISATIONS, MILITARY
PERSONNEL AND HUMANITARIAN AID WORKERS IN THE EXERCISE OF THEIR
FUNCTIONS, 
10. ETHNIC GERMAN RESETTLERS, 
11. PASSENGERS IN TRANSIT.
NOTE 4:
PAX OVER THE AGE OF 12 WHO AT ANY TIME DURING THE LAST TEN DAYS
PRIOR TO ENTRY HAVE STAYED IN AN AREA CLASSIFIED AT THE TIME OF
ENTRY AS 
A) AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF PARTICULAR
CONCERN THREATENS TO EMERGE MUST HAVE PROOF OF A NEGATIVE ANTIGEN
TEST ON ENTRY INTO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY, PROOF OF

B) AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF CONCERN

ON NUCLEIC ACID TESTING (PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC

E) ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY) WHEN ENTERING THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC
OF GERMANY, PROOF OF A NEGATIVE ANTIGEN TEST, OF RECOVERY OR
VACCINATION IS NOT SUFFICIENT IN THIS CASE.
ANTIGEN TEST: THE PROOF OF TESTING MUST REFER TO A TEST THAT WAS 
CARRIED OUT NO MORE THAN 48 HOURS BEFORE TIME OF ENTRY OR PLANNED 
TIME OF ENTRY INTO GERMANY.
NUCLEIC ACID TESTING (PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC 
ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY): THE PROOF OF TESTING MUST REFER 
TO A TEST THAT WAS CARRIED OUT NO MORE THAN 48 HOURS BEFORE TIME
OF OR PLANNED TIME OF DEPARTURE.
DESIGNATION OF AREAS OF CONCERN: CARRIERS ARE STRONGLY ADVISED TO
REGULARLY REVIEW THE DESIGNATION LIST. DESIGNATIONS ARE SUBJECT TO
CHANGE AT SHORT NOTICE.
NOTE 5:
AIRLINES MUST CHECK PROOF OF A NEGATIVE TEST FOR SARS-COV-2 (PCR,
POC-NAT, ANTIGEN OR EQUIVALENT) BEFORE BOARDING ON A RANDOM BASIS.
PAX OVER THE AGE OF 12 WHO AT ANY TIME DURING THE LAST TEN DAYS
PRIOR TO ENTRY TO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY HAVE STAYED IN A
VIRUS VARIANT AREA ARE ONLY PERMITTED TO BE CARRIED IF THEY HAVE
PROOF OF NEGATIVE TEST AS DEFINED IN NOTE 4.
CARRIERS CAN OFFER TESTS TO THEIR PASSENGERS, CARRY OUT THE TESTS
THEMSELVES OR CONTRACT THIRD PARTIES TO CARRY OUT THE TESTS.

E) ADDITIONAL RANDOM CHECKS BY THE FEDERAL POLICE/COMPETENT AUTHORITY
AT DESTINATION AIRPORT IN GERMANY.
CARRIERS TRANSPORTING PAX TO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY FROM A
VIRUS VARIANT AREA LOCATED IN A NON-SCHENGEN STATE MUST INFORM PAX
THAT PROOF OF NEGATIVE TEST MUST BE PRESENTED TO THE COMPETENT
AUTHORITIES UPON REQUEST DURING ENTRY CONTROL.
NOTE 7:
PAX OVER THE AGE OF 12 WHO AT ANY TIME DURING THE LAST TEN DAYS
PRIOR TO ENTRY HAVE STAYED IN AN AREA CLASSIFIED AT THE TIME OF
ENTRY AS A VIRUS-VARIANT AREA ARE OBLIGED BY LAW TO ACCEPT RANDOM
TESTING ON ENTRY.
NOTE 8:
CARRIERS ARE PROHIBITED TO TRANSPORT PAX FROM AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF
CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF PARTICULAR CONCERN ALREADY EXISTS TO
GERMANY. THIS RESTRICTION APPLIES TO ALL TRAVEL OF PAX ORIGINATING
FROM THIS AREA.
EXEMPTIONS: THE TRANSPORT BAN DOES NOT APPLY TO
- PAX HAVING GERMAN NATIONALITY AND PAX RESIDING AND WITH RIGHT

CHILDREN. IN THE CASE OF FLIGHTS FROM MEMBER STATES OF THE NORTHERN
IRELAND: THE TRANSPORT BAN DOES ALSO NOT APPLY TO PAX WITH A PARTNER
IN GERMANY (GERMAN NATIONALITY OR RIGHT OF RESIDENCE IN GERMANY)

- PAX TRANSITING A GERMAN AIRPORT INCLUDING TRANSIT FROM OR TO

- REPATRIATION OF AIRCRAFTS AND CREWS,
- TRANSPORTATION OF PERSONNEL IN THE INTEREST OF PUBLIC HEALTH,

notamdrec.notam_report: COVID-19: CARRIERS/CREWS/PASSENGER RESTRICTIONS AND REQUIREMENTS 1. RESTRICTIONS AND REQUIREMENTS NOTE 1: CARRIERS MUST PROVIDE INFORMATION REGARDING PASSENGER RESTRICTIONS AND REQUIREMENTS PUBLISHED BY THE GERMAN FEDERAL MINISTRY OF HEALTH TO ALL PAX. NOTE 2: PLEASE ADVISE PAX TO CHECK TRAVEL RESTRICTIONS, TESTING AND QUARANTINE OBLIGATIONS PRIOR TO DEPARTURE. NOTE 3: DUE TO RECIPROCITY RESERVATIONS ENTRY INTO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY IS PROHIBITED TO PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED IN THE FOLLOWING STATES: CHINA. THIS DOES NOT APPLY TO: 1. GERMAN CITIZENS, 2. EU CITIZENS, 3. CITIZENS OF LIECHTENSTEIN, SWITZERLAND, NORWAY OR ICELAND, 4.THIRD-COUNTRY NATIONALS WITH CURRENT RIGHT OF RESIDENCE IN PART 1 OF 9 GERMANY, OTHER EU COUNTRIES, LIECHTENSTEIN, SWITZERLAND, NORWAY OR ICELAND, 5. 1ST AND 2ND DEGREE RELATIVES (GRANDPARENTS, PARENTS, CHILDREN, GRANDCHILDREN AND SIBLINGS) OF PAX LISTED UNDER 1 - 4 ABOVE, 6. PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED IN HONG KONG, MACAO AND TAIWAN. PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED IN CHINA ARE PERMITTED TO ENTER THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY PROVIDED THEY HAVE AN IMPERATIVE NEED FOR TRAVEL: 1. HEALTHCARE WORKERS, HEALTH RESEARCHERS AND GERIATRIC CARE WORKERS, 2. SKILLED AND HIGHLY QUALIFIED FOREIGN WORKERS IF THEIR EMPLOYMENT AN ECONOMIC PERSPECTIVE AND THE WORK CANNOT BE POSTPONED OR PERFORMEDABROAD, 3. FREIGHT TRANSPORT AND OTHER TRANSPORT PERSONNEL, 4. SEASONAL WORKERS IN AGRICULTURE, 5. SEAFARERS, 6. FOREIGN STUDENTS, TRAINEES, VOLUNTEERS, 7. PERSONS IMMIGRATING INTO GERMANY FOR THE PURPOSE OF JOINING THEIR FAMILIES AND VISITS FOR URGENT FAMILY REASONS OR SHORT TERM VISITS OF CORE FAMILY MEMBERS (HUSBAND/WIFE, MINOR CHILDREN, PARENTS OF MINOR CHILDREN) OR UNMARRIED PARTNERS IN A RELATIONSHIP WITH GERMAN NATIONALS, PART 2 OF 9 EU CITIZENS AND THIRD-COUNTRY NATIONALS WITH CURRENT RIGHT OF RESIDENCE IN GERMANY OR JOINT SHORT TERM VISITS OF COUPLES (THIRD COUNTRY NATIONAL AND GERMAN NATIONAL/EU CITIZEN) RESIDING TOGETHER INA THIRD COUNTRY FOR IMPORTANT REASONS, 8. PERSONS IN NEED OF INTERNATIONAL PROTECTION OR FOR OTHER HUMANITARIAN REASONS, 9. DIPLOMATS, STAFF OF INTERNATIONAL ORGANISATIONS, MILITARY PERSONNEL AND HUMANITARIAN AID WORKERS IN THE EXERCISE OF THEIR FUNCTIONS, 10. ETHNIC GERMAN RESETTLERS, 11. PASSENGERS IN TRANSIT. NOTE 4: PAX OVER THE AGE OF 12 WHO AT ANY TIME DURING THE LAST TEN DAYS PRIOR TO ENTRY HAVE STAYED IN AN AREA CLASSIFIED AT THE TIME OF ENTRY AS A) AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF PARTICULAR CONCERN THREATENS TO EMERGE MUST HAVE PROOF OF A NEGATIVE ANTIGEN TEST ON ENTRY INTO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY, PROOF OF NEGATIVE TEST BASED ON PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY ARE ALSO PERMISSIBLE. PROOF OF RECOVERY OR VACCINATION IS NOT SUFFICIENT IN THIS CASE. B) AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF CONCERN PARTICULAR ALREADY EXISTS MUST HAVE PROOF OF A NEGATIVE TEST BASED ON NUCLEIC ACID TESTING (PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC PART 3 OF 9 ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY) WHEN ENTERING THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY, PROOF OF A NEGATIVE ANTIGEN TEST, OF RECOVERY OR VACCINATION IS NOT SUFFICIENT IN THIS CASE. ANTIGEN TEST: THE PROOF OF TESTING MUST REFER TO A TEST THAT WAS CARRIED OUT NO MORE THAN 48 HOURS BEFORE TIME OF ENTRY OR PLANNED TIME OF ENTRY INTO GERMANY. NUCLEIC ACID TESTING (PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY): THE PROOF OF TESTING MUST REFER TO A TEST THAT WAS CARRIED OUT NO MORE THAN 48 HOURS BEFORE TIME OF OR PLANNED TIME OF DEPARTURE. DESIGNATION OF AREAS OF CONCERN: CARRIERS ARE STRONGLY ADVISED TO REGULARLY REVIEW THE DESIGNATION LIST. DESIGNATIONS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE AT SHORT NOTICE. NOTE 5: AIRLINES MUST CHECK PROOF OF A NEGATIVE TEST FOR SARS-COV-2 (PCR, POC-NAT, ANTIGEN OR EQUIVALENT) BEFORE BOARDING ON A RANDOM BASIS. PAX OVER THE AGE OF 12 WHO AT ANY TIME DURING THE LAST TEN DAYS PRIOR TO ENTRY TO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY HAVE STAYED IN A VIRUS VARIANT AREA ARE ONLY PERMITTED TO BE CARRIED IF THEY HAVE PROOF OF NEGATIVE TEST AS DEFINED IN NOTE 4. CARRIERS CAN OFFER TESTS TO THEIR PASSENGERS, CARRY OUT THE TESTS THEMSELVES OR CONTRACT THIRD PARTIES TO CARRY OUT THE TESTS. NOTE 6: A PROOF OF NEGATIVE TEST FOR SARS-COV-2 IS SUBJECT TO PART 4 OF 9 ADDITIONAL RANDOM CHECKS BY THE FEDERAL POLICE/COMPETENT AUTHORITY AT DESTINATION AIRPORT IN GERMANY. CARRIERS TRANSPORTING PAX TO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY FROM A VIRUS VARIANT AREA LOCATED IN A NON-SCHENGEN STATE MUST INFORM PAX THAT PROOF OF NEGATIVE TEST MUST BE PRESENTED TO THE COMPETENT AUTHORITIES UPON REQUEST DURING ENTRY CONTROL. NOTE 7: PAX OVER THE AGE OF 12 WHO AT ANY TIME DURING THE LAST TEN DAYS PRIOR TO ENTRY HAVE STAYED IN AN AREA CLASSIFIED AT THE TIME OF ENTRY AS A VIRUS-VARIANT AREA ARE OBLIGED BY LAW TO ACCEPT RANDOM TESTING ON ENTRY. NOTE 8: CARRIERS ARE PROHIBITED TO TRANSPORT PAX FROM AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF PARTICULAR CONCERN ALREADY EXISTS TO GERMANY. THIS RESTRICTION APPLIES TO ALL TRAVEL OF PAX ORIGINATING FROM THIS AREA. EXEMPTIONS: THE TRANSPORT BAN DOES NOT APPLY TO - PAX HAVING GERMAN NATIONALITY AND PAX RESIDING AND WITH RIGHT EUROPEAN UNION OR THE UNITED KINGDOM OF GREAT BRITAIN AND OF RESIDENCE IN GERMANY AS WELL AS THEIR SPOUSES, PARTNERS FROM THE SAME HOUSEHOLD, MINOR CHILDREN AND PARENTS ACCOMPANYING THEIR MINOR CHILDREN. IN THE CASE OF FLIGHTS FROM MEMBER STATES OF THE NORTHERN IRELAND: THE TRANSPORT BAN DOES ALSO NOT APPLY TO PAX WITH A PARTNER IN GERMANY (GERMAN NATIONALITY OR RIGHT OF RESIDENCE IN GERMANY) PART 5 OF 9 WHO DOES NOT BELONG TO THE SAME HOUSEHOLD, - PAX TRANSITING A GERMAN AIRPORT INCLUDING TRANSIT FROM OR TO ANOTHER SCHENGEN COUNTRY, - EXCLUSIVELY CARGO OR POSTAL OR FERRY FLIGHTS, - REPATRIATION OF AIRCRAFTS AND CREWS, - TRANSPORTATION OF PERSONNEL IN THE INTEREST OF PUBLIC HEALTH, - AMBULANCE FLIGHTS AND FLIGHTS TRANSPORTING TRANSPLANT ORGANS AND NECESSARY ACCOMPANYING PERSONNEL, - FLIGHTS FOR URGENT HUMANITARIAN REASONS, - FLIGHTS ON BEHALF OF THE EURATOM SAFEGUARDS, THE INTERNATIONAL ATOMIC ENERGY AGENCY, THE UNITED NATIONS AND ITS AGENCIES, THE EUROPEAN UNION AND THE EUROPEAN CENTRE FOR MEDIUM-RANGE WEATHER HOUSEHOLD AND MINOR CHILDREN WHOSE APPOINTMENT AND ARRIVAL HAS FORECASTS, - MEMBERS OF A FOREIGN DIPLOMATIC MISSION OR CONSULAR OFFICE AS WELL AS THEIR ACCOMPANYING SPOUSES, PARTNERS FROM THE SAME BEEN NOTIFIED TO THE FEDERAL FOREIGN OFFICE, - TRANSPORT OF PERSONS ACCREDITED BY THE RESPECTIVE ORGANISING COMMITTEE FOR THE PREPARATION, PARTICIPATION, IMPLEMENTATION AND FOLLOW-UP OF INTERNATIONAL SPORTING EVENTS, - TRANSPORTS OF VACCINATED PAX FOR WHICH THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT OF GERMANY HAS CONFIRMED THAT THEIR TRANSPORT IS IN THE NATIONAL INTEREST.   PART 1 OF 9
  
  GERMANY, OTHER EU COUNTRIES, LIECHTENSTEIN, SWITZERLAND, NORWAY
  OR ICELAND,
  5. 1ST AND 2ND DEGREE RELATIVES (GRANDPARENTS, PARENTS,
  CHILDREN, GRANDCHILDREN AND SIBLINGS) OF PAX LISTED UNDER 1 - 4
  ABOVE,
  6. PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED IN HONG KONG, MACAO
  AND TAIWAN.
  PAX WHO HAVE RESIDED AND LAST STAYED IN CHINA ARE PERMITTED TO
  ENTER THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY PROVIDED THEY HAVE AN
  IMPERATIVE NEED FOR TRAVEL:
  1. HEALTHCARE WORKERS, HEALTH RESEARCHERS AND GERIATRIC CARE
  WORKERS,
  2. SKILLED AND HIGHLY QUALIFIED FOREIGN WORKERS IF THEIR
  EMPLOYMENT AN ECONOMIC PERSPECTIVE AND THE WORK CANNOT BE
  POSTPONED OR PERFORMEDABROAD,
  3. FREIGHT TRANSPORT AND OTHER TRANSPORT PERSONNEL,
  4. SEASONAL WORKERS IN AGRICULTURE,
  5. SEAFARERS,
  6. FOREIGN STUDENTS, TRAINEES, VOLUNTEERS,
  7. PERSONS IMMIGRATING INTO GERMANY
  FOR THE PURPOSE OF JOINING THEIR FAMILIES AND VISITS FOR
  URGENT FAMILY REASONS OR SHORT TERM VISITS OF CORE FAMILY MEMBERS
  (HUSBAND/WIFE, MINOR CHILDREN, PARENTS OF MINOR CHILDREN) OR
  UNMARRIED PARTNERS IN A RELATIONSHIP WITH GERMAN NATIONALS,
  PART 2 OF 9
  
  EU CITIZENS AND THIRD-COUNTRY NATIONALS WITH CURRENT RIGHT OF
  RESIDENCE IN GERMANY OR JOINT SHORT TERM VISITS OF COUPLES (THIRD
  COUNTRY NATIONAL AND GERMAN NATIONAL/EU CITIZEN) RESIDING TOGETHER
  INA THIRD COUNTRY FOR IMPORTANT REASONS,
  8. PERSONS IN NEED OF INTERNATIONAL PROTECTION OR FOR OTHER
  HUMANITARIAN REASONS,
  9. DIPLOMATS, STAFF OF INTERNATIONAL ORGANISATIONS, MILITARY
  PERSONNEL AND HUMANITARIAN AID WORKERS IN THE EXERCISE OF THEIR
  FUNCTIONS,
  10. ETHNIC GERMAN RESETTLERS,
  11. PASSENGERS IN TRANSIT.
  NOTE 4:
  PAX OVER THE AGE OF 12 WHO AT ANY TIME DURING THE LAST TEN DAYS
  PRIOR TO ENTRY HAVE STAYED IN AN AREA CLASSIFIED AT THE TIME OF
  ENTRY AS
  A) AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF PARTICULAR
  CONCERN THREATENS TO EMERGE MUST HAVE PROOF OF A NEGATIVE ANTIGEN
  TEST ON ENTRY INTO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY, PROOF OF
  NEGATIVE TEST BASED ON PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC
  ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY ARE ALSO PERMISSIBLE. PROOF OF
  RECOVERY OR VACCINATION IS NOT SUFFICIENT IN THIS CASE.
  B) AN AREA OF VARIANTS OF CONCERN IN WHICH A VARIANT OF CONCERN
  PARTICULAR ALREADY EXISTS MUST HAVE PROOF OF A NEGATIVE TEST BASED
  ON NUCLEIC ACID TESTING (PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC
  PART 3 OF 9
  
  ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY) WHEN ENTERING THE FEDERAL
  REPUBLIC OF GERMANY, PROOF OF A NEGATIVE ANTIGEN TEST, OF RECOVERY
  OR VACCINATION IS NOT SUFFICIENT IN THIS CASE.
  ANTIGEN TEST: THE PROOF OF TESTING MUST REFER TO A TEST THAT WAS
  CARRIED OUT NO MORE THAN 48 HOURS BEFORE TIME OF ENTRY OR PLANNED
  TIME OF ENTRY INTO GERMANY.
  NUCLEIC ACID TESTING (PCR, POC-NAT OR OTHER METHODS OF NUCLEIC
  ACID AMPLIFICATION TECHNOLOGY): THE PROOF OF TESTING MUST REFER TO
  A TEST THAT WAS CARRIED OUT NO MORE THAN 48 HOURS BEFORE TIME OF
  OR PLANNED TIME OF DEPARTURE.

  REGULARLY REVIEW THE DESIGNATION LIST. DESIGNATIONS ARE SUBJECT TO
  CHANGE AT SHORT NOTICE.

  AIRLINES MUST CHECK PROOF OF A NEGATIVE TEST FOR SARS-COV-2 (PCR,
  POC-NAT, ANTIGEN OR EQUIVALENT) BEFORE BOARDING ON A RANDOM BASIS.

  PRIOR TO ENTRY TO THE FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF GERMANY HAVE STAYED IN A
  VIRUS VARIANT AREA ARE ONLY PERMITTED TO BE CARRIED IF THEY HAVE
  PROOF OF NEGATIVE TEST AS DEFINED IN NOTE 4.
  CARRIERS CAN OFFER TESTS TO THEIR PASSENGERS, CARRY OUT THE TESTS
  THEMSELVES OR CONTRACT THIRD PARTIES TO CARRY OUT THE TESTS.

  ADDITIONAL RANDOM CHECKS BY THE FEDERAL POLICE/COMPETENT

  SUBJECT: AUTO COST INDEXES

  EITHER SELECT A SPECIFIC COST INDEX NUMBER FROM THE LIST, OR THEY
  MAY SELECT "AUTO". WHEN PLANNING AN "AUTO" COST INDEX, THE SYSTEM
  WILL REFERENCE THE SCHEDULED "TIME ENROUTE" OPTION AND ATTEMPT TO
  CHOOSE A COST INDEX WHICH CLOSELY MATCHES THIS VALUE. NOTE THAT
  THE "TIME ENROUTE" OPTION IS MEANT AS A GATE TO GATE TIME (AS
  INDICATED ON AN AIRLINE'S FLIGHT SCHEDULE, FOR EXAMPLE). IF A
  "TIME ENROUTE" OF 2:30 IS SELECTED, THE SYSTEM WILL SUBTRACT THE
  TAXI TIMES FROM THIS VALUE TO DETERMINE THE SCHEDULED AIR TIME. IT
  WILL THEN DETERMINE AND USE THE COST INDEX WHICH MATCHES THIS AIR
  TIME.
